Introduction

3YE (Pronounced “Third Eye”) was a 3-member girl group under GH Entertainment composed of former members of GH Entertainments’ previous girl group Apple.B. They debuted on May 21, 2019 with their first digital single, “DMT (Do Ma Thang)”.

On November 14, 2024, their contracts with GH Entertainment officially expired, leading to their disbandment.
